"title": "1055: God, grace and mercy of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1055: god, grace and mercy of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The qualities of God's character by which he shows himself compassionate, accepting, and generous to sinful human beings, shielding them from his wrath, forgiving them, and bestowing on them his righteousness so that they can live and grow in faith and obedience. Grace and mercy are particularly expressed through God's covenant with his chosen people and through Jesus Christ's atoning death on the cross.</p>\n<h2>God's grace and mercy are made known in Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:16-John1:17\">JHN 1:16–1:17</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The abundance of God's grace and mercy</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:4-Eph2:8\">EPH 2:4–2:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam24:14\">2SA 24:14</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr21:13\">1CH 21:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:13\">PSA 69:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps84:11\">PSA 84:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps102:13\">PSA 102:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:4\">ROM 2:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:17\">ROM 5:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:23\">ROM 9:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:14\">1TI 1:14</a></p>\n<h2>God's grace and mercy are always unearned and unmerited</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:7-Deut7:8\">DEU 7:7–7:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:5-Deut9:6\">DEU 9:5–9:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:22\">EZK 36:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:18\">DAN 9:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:16\">ROM 9:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:6\">EPH 1:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:8-Eph2:9\">EPH 2:8–2:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:8\">EPH 3:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:5\">TIT 3:5</a></p>\n<h2>God's grace and mercy are a source of blessing</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:1-Gen21:2\">GEN 21:1–21:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen33:11\">GEN 33:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:21\">1SA 2:21</a></p>\n<h2>God's grace and mercy are expressed in the covenant relationship</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:3\">JER 31:3</a></strong> <em>Hebrew “hesed” (translated as “love”, “loving-kindness”, “unfailing love”) expresses specifically the grace and mercy that underlie the covenant relationship.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:6\">EXO 34:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:9\">DEU 7:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:12\">DEU 7:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:17\">NEH 9:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps6:4\">PSA 6:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:3\">ISA 55:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:22\">LAM 3:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:32\">LAM 3:32</a></p>\n<h2>Salvation comes by grace</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:11\">TIT 2:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:25-Mark10:27\">MRK 10:25–10:27</a> <em>Jesus Christ's words to his disciples</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:15\">ROM 5:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:5-Eph1:6\">EPH 1:5–1:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:8\">EPH 2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:9-2Tim1:10\">2TI 1:9–1:10</a></p>\n<h3>This is ultimately shown in the cross of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:24-Rom3:25\">ROM 3:24–3:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:8\">ROM 5:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:7\">EPH 1:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:9\">HEB 2:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:10-2Pet1:11\">2PE 1:10–1:11</a></p>\n<h2>God's grace and mercy are offered to sinners</h2>\n<h3>Punishment is withheld</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra9:13\">EZR 9:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs13:22-2Kgs13:23\">2KI 13:22–13:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:15-Ezek20:17\">EZK 20:15–20:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos11:8\">HOS 11:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:13\">JOL 2:13</a></p>\n<h3>Sin is forgiven</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:18\">MIC 7:18</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:9\">1JN 1:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps32:5\">PSA 32:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov28:13\">PRO 28:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:7\">ISA 55:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:12\">JER 3:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer33:8\">JER 33:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:9\">DAN 9:9</a></p>\n<h3>Sinners' prayers are heard</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:1\">PSA 51:1</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:13-Luke18:14\">LUK 18:13–18:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps6:2-Ps6:3\">PSA 6:2–6:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps123:3\">PSA 123:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab3:2\">HAB 3:2</a></p>\n<h2>The favour of God</h2>\n<h3>Examples of those who found favour with God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:4\">GEN 4:4</a> <em>Abel</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:8\">GEN 6:8</a> <em>Noah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:12\">EXO 33:12</a> <em>Moses</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:17-Judg6:18\">JDG 6:17–6:18</a> <em>Gideon</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:26\">1SA 2:26</a> <em>Samuel</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra7:27-Ezra7:28\">EZR 7:27–7:28</a> <em>Ezra</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:30\">LUK 1:30</a> <em>Mary</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:52\">LUK 2:52</a> <em>Jesus Christ</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:46\">ACT 7:46</a> <em>David</em></p>\n<h3>Examples of those who seek the favour of God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:11\">EXO 32:11</a> <em>Moses</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs13:4\">2KI 13:4</a> <em>Jehoahaz</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr33:12\">2CH 33:12</a> <em>Manasseh</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh5:19\">NEH 5:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:31\">NEH 13:31</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:17\">DAN 9:17</a> <em>Daniel</em></p>\n<h3>Promises relating to the favour of God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:9\">LEV 26:9</a> <em>It is given to the obedient (see <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:3\">Lev 26:3</a>)</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps5:12\">PSA 5:12</a> <em>It is given to the righteous</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps30:5\">PSA 30:5</a> <em>It lasts for a lifetime.</em></p>\n<h3>The OT predicts a future age of God's favour</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:8\">ISA 49:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa60:10\">ISA 60:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:2\">ISA 61:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:9\">EZK 36:9</a></p>\n<h2>Implications for believers of the grace and mercy of God</h2>\n<h3>God's grace and mercy are to influence the character and conduct of believers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:1-Rom6:2\">ROM 6:1–6:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:23\">ACT 11:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:14\">ROM 6:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:1\">ROM 12:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:11-Titus2:12\">TIT 2:11–2:12</a></p>\n<h3>Believers must humbly rely on God's grace and mercy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:21\">GAL 2:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:34\">PRO 3:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:6\">JAS 4:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah2:8\">JON 2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:4\">ROM 2:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:1-2Cor6:2\">2CO 6:1–6:2</a></p>\n<h3>God's grace strengthens believers for service</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:7-Eph3:8\">EPH 3:7–3:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:10\">1CO 3:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:7-2Cor12:9\">2CO 12:7–12:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:15-Gal1:16\">GAL 1:15–1:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:7\">EPH 4:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:11\">EPH 4:11</a></p>\n<h2>Illustrations of God's grace and mercy</h2>\n<p>God shows grace to Noah, saving him from the flood and afterwards establishing a covenant with him:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:8\">GEN 6:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:22\">GEN 6:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen9:9-Gen9:11\">GEN 9:9–9:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah1:1-Jonah1:3\">JON 1:1–1:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah1:17\">JON 1:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah2:1-Jonah2:3\">JON 2:1–2:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah3:1-Jonah3:10\">JON 3:1–3:10</a> <em>God shows mercy in saving first Jonah and then (following their repentance) the people of Nineveh</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:11-Luke15:32\">LUK 15:11–15:32</a> <em>The forgiving love of the prodigal's father illustrates the divine mercy of God.</em></p>",
